= Social Patriotism Emerges

A newer faction of young and old <span style="color: #f0456a;">socialists</span>, led by ADGB unionist Lothar Erdmann, is rallying under the banner of "Social Patriotism." This group calls for a renewed bond between the workers, <span style="color: #c00000;">socialism</span>, and the nation. Erdmann is the architect of the ADGB's nationalist shift in recent years, including its sharpened rhetoric against the Treaty of Versailles.

This is plainly Schleicher’s handiwork—yet this emerging faction now holds real sway within our party, given the Chancellor’s grip on our more "patriotic" and loosely <span style="color: #9B0000;">Marxist</span> trade unions.

- @socpat_pro: Who said patriotism and <span style="color: #c00000;">socialism</span> aren't compatible?
- @socpat_against: There's no war but the class war.

